    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## WA-Inbound-Orchestrator\n\n### Setup WhatsApp Cloud API\n1. Crear credencial 'WhatsApp Cloud API' tipo Header Auth:\n   - Name: Authorization\n   - Value: Bearer YOUR_WA_TOKEN\n2. Configurar webhook URL en Meta Developer Console\n3. Para verificacion GET, usar otro webhook o verificar manualmente\n\n### Credenciales necesarias\n- **Postgres Clinica**: conexion a BD\n- **WhatsApp Cloud API**: Header Auth con Bearer token\n- **OpenAI**: API key para GPT-4o\n\n### Schema SQL\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE conversation_sessions (\n  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  phone VARCHAR(20) UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n  session_data JSONB DEFAULT '{}',\n  last_interaction TIMESTAMP,\n  appointment_context JSONB DEFAULT '{}',\n  updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE agent_memory (\n  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  session_id VARCHAR(100),\n  messages JSONB DEFAULT '[]',\n  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE workflow_errors (\n  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  workflow VARCHAR(100),\n  error_message TEXT,\n  phone VARCHAR(20),\n  payload JSONB,\n  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()\n);\n```",
        "height": 824,
        "width": 588
      },
      "id": "sticky-note",
      "name": "Sticky Note - Schema SQL y Setup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        0,
        -512
      ]
    }
